snippet.textDisplay: Reduce a beer till it turns color, Brown ground meat, add chile powder, sage, cilantro, re-fried beans, salsa, BBQ sauce.  You could bury your ingredients in any one of the ingredients and the chile will still be chile, and pretty good; so the ammounts wouldn't matter at all: you could make it cheap or not, just get all eight ingredients in there and the worst you'll get is 'good-chile'.  if someone doesn't like cilantro, just put it in anyway and say there isn't any and take that to your grave.
snippet.textOriginal: Reduce a beer till it turns color, Brown ground meat, add chile powder, sage, cilantro, re-fried beans, salsa, BBQ sauce.
